WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.003 --> 00:00:02.936
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: So
if I have an h1 right here, so

2
00:00:02.936 --> 00:00:08.175
then I wanted to make this h1 red,
something like this.

3
00:00:08.175 --> 00:00:09.931
So how would I do that?

4
00:00:09.931 --> 00:00:12.756
You can't do that with just html.

5
00:00:12.756 --> 00:00:16.071
You need something else to come in and
affect that.

6
00:00:16.071 --> 00:00:20.438
So we're gonna write CSS
rule to make that the case.

7
00:00:20.438 --> 00:00:22.269
So that is going to look like this.

8
00:00:22.269 --> 00:00:24.196
This is what CSS looks like.

9
00:00:26.524 --> 00:00:29.117
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: So
let's break down all of the pieces here.

10
00:00:30.372 --> 00:00:32.857
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: I have an h1 right here,
