11
00:00:32.857 --> 00:00:36.560
This is called the selector.

12
00:00:36.560 --> 00:00:38.621
The selector selects.

13
00:00:38.621 --> 00:00:40.513
I think that follows, right?

14
00:00:40.513 --> 00:00:45.555
So in this case, it's gonna say,
every h1 on the page, if it is an h1,

15
00:00:45.555 --> 00:00:49.553
then apply everything between
the curly braces, okay?

16
00:00:49.553 --> 00:00:52.077
So,these are called curly braces,
in case you didn't know.

17
00:00:54.127 --> 00:00:58.429
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: [COUGH] So it's apply
everything between the curly braces.

18
00:00:58.429 --> 00:01:01.021
Now we only have one.

19
00:01:01.021 --> 00:01:04.559
Thing to apply between the curly braces.

20
00:01:04.559 --> 00:01:07.374
We say the color red.

21
00:01:07.374 --> 00:01:10.343
Color is called a property.

22
00:01:10.343 --> 00:01:14.224
So there's how many properties.

23
00:01:14.224 --> 00:01:15.040
I said it right there.

24
00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:17.374
There are about 350 properties.

25
00:01:17.374 --> 00:01:22.222
This is a lot like HTML that
you really are only gonna use,

26
00:01:22.222 --> 00:01:25.457
again, maybe 50 to 100 of them.

27
00:01:25.457 --> 00:01:29.705
There's a lot, and there are people
that are better at this than I am,

28
00:01:29.705 --> 00:01:31.945
that will probably use more things.

29
00:01:31.945 --> 00:01:36.438
But for the most part, there's gonna be
about 50 of them that you're gonna use

30
00:01:36.438 --> 00:01:40.093
a lot, and then the rest you're rarely,
if ever, going to use.

31
00:01:40.093 --> 00:01:42.546
So color, as you may imagine,
is quite useful.

32
00:01:42.546 --> 00:01:44.047
We use it quite a bit.

33
00:01:44.047 --> 00:01:48.877
So color is going to
change the font color.

34
00:01:48.877 --> 00:01:50.031
That's just what it does.

35
00:01:50.031 --> 00:01:54.189
It's one of those things where you just
have to know what these things do.

36
00:01:54.189 --> 00:01:55.146
And you can always Google it.

37
00:01:55.146 --> 00:01:57.438
You could just Google how
do I change font color, and

38
00:01:57.438 --> 00:02:00.055
I guarantee you it would be one
of the first things on there.

39
00:02:00.055 --> 00:02:07.211
So,
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: Then I'd put red here.

40
00:02:07.211 --> 00:02:14.281
This is called the value, and red happens
to be a value that CSS understands.

41
00:02:14.281 --> 00:02:16.468
It understands what red means.

42
00:02:16.468 --> 00:02:19.003
So that's why this works.

43
00:02:19.003 --> 00:02:21.055
It turns the color red.

44
00:02:22.999 --> 00:02:24.315
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: We saw hex before.

45
00:02:24.315 --> 00:02:26.029
You can also put hex here.

46
00:02:26.029 --> 00:02:29.497
The fact that I put right here,
all the ones that CSS understands.

47
00:02:29.497 --> 00:02:32.528
It understands a bunch of
different ways of doing color.

48
00:02:32.528 --> 00:02:35.519
It understands hexadecimal.

49
00:02:35.519 --> 00:02:37.268
It understands RGB.

50
00:02:37.268 --> 00:02:40.172
This is how you would do RGB, right here.

51
00:02:40.172 --> 00:02:42.801
And it also understands HSL.

52
00:02:42.801 --> 00:02:47.471
Which I do not know nearly enough
about HSL, it stands for hue,

53
00:02:47.471 --> 00:02:50.484
saturation, and lightness, I think.

54
00:02:50.484 --> 00:02:54.068
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: Luminosity [INAUDIBLE]
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: Luminosity,

55
00:02:54.068 --> 00:02:58.443
it's a mystery, I'm just kidding.

56
00:02:58.443 --> 00:02:59.994
I don't know, I never use it,
I'll put it that way.

57
00:02:59.994 --> 00:03:06.754
[LAUGH] And then it understands a hundred
and fifty what are called named colors.

58
00:03:06.754 --> 00:03:09.113
And there's some really
weird named colors.

59
00:03:10.891 --> 00:03:14.287
&gt;&gt; Brian Holt: But if you wanna understand
more about like how CSS can do colors,

60
00:03:14.287 --> 00:03:16.754
